track_notes: Parked on rough track near to gate. Route both ways uses access land. Operated against fence next to small pond on summit.
This route will take you from a convenient parking area (Room for around 10 cars) out via the windfarm road, then back via the Limers Gate path.
track_title: Freeholds Top via the Wind Farm

track_notes: I parked outside domestic properties in Shawforth. Please be considerate of home-owners of course. Proceed up concrete road just south of Mercedes garage. Straightforward ascent most of the way. Near the top if you follow the PRoW when last tried there were some obstructions, so instead I found it better sticking more north-east

This is a track from the Yorkshire side of the summit. There is parking on the verge on a side road at SD92652186. Head west towards Brown Road Farm. There are numerous tracks - you can keep out of the way of the farm, along the track slightly to its north. There were lots of cows with calves. Strike WNW off the track at SD91742192 where there is a finger post (minus its finger). The faint track takes you just south of a pylon. Once you reach the stile at SD91402203 it is quite obvious. Workers were busy attending a large plantation of saplings so no doubt it will be pleasantly wooded eventually.

Total time (including ops): 1h 40m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
